            <!-- Introduction -->
            <div type="introduction">
                <head>Introduction</head>
                <lg>
                    <l>Father, what is a Legislature?</l>
                    <l>A representative body elected by the people of the state.</l>
                    <l>Are women people?</l>
                    <l>No, my son, criminals, lunatics and women are not people.</l>
                    <l>Do legislators legislate for nothing?</l>
                    <l>Oh, no; they are paid a salary.</l>
                    <l>By whom?</l>
                    <l>By the people.</l>
                    <l>Are women people?</l>
                    <l>Of course, my son, just as much as men are.</l>
                </lg>
                <note>
                    <p>To the New York Tribune, in whose generous columns many of these verses first appeared, the author here wishes to express her gratitude.</p>
                </note>
            </div>
            
